Can you explain more about response time? Is it now important to miner to stay close to validator, since hard disk latency is likely few ms, but network latency will be huge compare to it. So people who stay close validator with HDD storage will outperform miner with SSD and NVMe?
Pinned a message.

I understand your concern, but the reason I took response time into consideration is that I encountered several miners who have created their own local environment to provide one huge storage. This has caused an increase in disk-access latency.

As for network latency, validators are located in different areas (some in EU, some in US, and some in Asia), resulting in distributed network latency. This means that a miner near validator A will be scored highly by validator A, but low by validator B, ensuring fairness in the scoring process.
Please make sure if you local subtensor is working without any issues.

Would you be ready for a DTAO upgrade this week?
We will provide you with a document with some simple design information + how to upgrade your network

Hi @ here: 

We will be shortly upgrading the testnet chain with Dynamic TAO. 
In order to prepare testnet subnet for this change read this document: https://docs.bittensor.com/dynamic-tao

It is essential that your upgrade your Bittensor version to work with the new chain (we will inform you when that has been done) or else some of the common commands your miners/validators use i.e. like `subtensor.metagraph` to retrieve the latest network state ***will fail***. Please read the above document explaining how you can change to the correct branch and avoid this situation.

Aside from the upgrade to the SDK and CLI, you should experience very little change in the actual consensus of your network. Why? because the normal TAO staked on your validators will still be counted in each mechanism. Within the next month or more your subnet token will begin to have more effect on the dynamics of Yuma Consensus. We will be releasing more information on how this work technically later.

We will do our best to explain more about this upgrade and what you need to know at todays Novelty Search. Please come at the usual time of Thursday, January 9, 2025 3:00:00 PM today.

Best
